  "texts": [
    "The attention mechanism assigns to each input component (like a text symbol) a score quantifying its relevance to the context of the other input components, based on the statistical dependencies detected.",
    "The set of these scores for the different input components forms an attention map (see for example Fig. 4c).",
    "Generative models: models that perform density estimation, i.e., they reconstruct the probability distribution from which the data have been generated, supporting the design of synthetic data by sampling from the learnt distribution.",
    "For sequence data, generative models range from probability distributions obtained simply from the frequencies of symbols at each position (independentsite models, see for example Fig. 2a), to probability distributions specified by shallow ML architectures like RBMs or by deep generative language models based on transformers, RNNs and LSTMs.",
    "Other generative ML architectures increasingly employed in protein modeling are variational autoencoders 202, generative adversarial networks 203, and diffusion models 204."
  ],
